{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/shakyo-at-home/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"bf7b47d8-6493-5c4b-8653-11d87d43918c","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/1f853/shakyo_1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/01472/shakyo_1.webp 240w,\n/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/222bd/shakyo_1.webp 480w,\n/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/620b9/shakyo_1.webp 960w,\n/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/86447/shakyo_1.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/3bc27/shakyo_1.jpg 240w,\n/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/98431/shakyo_1.jpg 480w,\n/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/b3ee8/shakyo_1.jpg 960w,\n/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/1f853/shakyo_1.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/db5405fb7d08689e5d0a55f402f1d1b8/b3ee8/shakyo_1.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Shakyo_1\"\n          title=\"Shakyo_1\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>  </p>\n<p>写経(Shakyo) means Japanese calligraphy to copy Buddhist sutra text in this case.  </p>\n<p>Everyday I copy 般若心経(the Heart Sutra) by hand at my home.<br>\nIt all started when I felt very much that I wanted to commemorate my ancestors and friend’s death in this past September.  </p>\n<p>I refer to the following page to do Shakyo.<br>\n<a href=\"http://www.koyasan.or.jp/experience/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://www.koyasan.or.jp/experience/</a><br>\n(写経 > experience02 仏教と写経 > 詳しく見る > 写経作用を知る)  </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/1f853/shakyo_2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/01472/shakyo_2.webp 240w,\n/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/222bd/shakyo_2.webp 480w,\n/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/620b9/shakyo_2.webp 960w,\n/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/86447/shakyo_2.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/3bc27/shakyo_2.jpg 240w,\n/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/98431/shakyo_2.jpg 480w,\n/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/b3ee8/shakyo_2.jpg 960w,\n/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/1f853/shakyo_2.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/538b47644d29b1eadfe1e242b71b57e3/b3ee8/shakyo_2.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Shakyo_2\"\n          title=\"Shakyo_2\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>  </p>\n<p>If I make a writing mistake, I rewrite this way.  </p>\n<p>I hope this will help them.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/shakyo-at-home/","tagSlugs":["/tag/buddhism/","/tag/shakyo/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-11-15T10:00:00Z","description":"写経(Shakyo) means Japanese calligraphy to copy Buddhist sutra text in this case. Everyday I copy 般若心経(the...","tags":["Buddhism","Shakyo"],"title":"Shakyo at Home","socialImage":"/media/191115/shakyo_1.jpg"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/shakyo-at-home/"}}}